-- Bancolombia issues $494.6 million in subordinate bonds
-- By Nelson Bocanegra
-- Wed Sep 24, 2014 04:10PM EDT
-- None



BOGOTA, Sept 24 (Reuters) - Bancolombia, Colombia's largest bank, issued 988 billion pesos ($494.6 million) in subordinate bonds on the local market on Wednesday, the stock exchange said in a statement.

Bancolombia <BIC.CN> offered 10-year paper at a yield equivalent to the consumer price index (CPI) plus 4.29 percent, 15-year bonds at CPI plus 4.65 percent and the 20-year bonds at CPI plus 4.79 percent.  The bank received offers for 1.25 trillion pesos' worth of bonds during the issue, which is the first in a global quota of 3 trillion pesos ($1.5 billion). The funds raised will go to the company's banking operations. The bank's subordinate bonds have a AA+ rating from Fitch Ratings.